<p><strong>Prep time</strong>: 25 min | <strong>Cook time: </strong>45 mins</p>
<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Olive oil ( 2tbsp )</li>
<li>Onion </li>
<li>2 Garlic cloves</li>
<li>Bell pepper</li>
<li>Mushrooms</li>
<li>Tomato Puree</li>
<li>Tomato Paste </li>
<li>Lean beef mince ( 500g )</li>
<li>Mozzerella </li>
<li>Chedder</li>
<li>Basil</li>
<li>Jalepeno</li>
<li>Oregano</li>
<li>Beef Stock ( 1 cube )</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>White Sauce</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Salted butter ( 2tbsp )</li>
<li>All purpose flour ( 2tbsp )</li>
<li>Milk ( 2cups; warm )</li>
<li>Pepper</li>
<li>Nutmeg</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Other</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Lasagne sheets  (10 - 13 )</li>
<li>Parmesean</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Instructions</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Heat oil in pot, at medium heat</li>
<li>Add diced onions,bell peppers &amp; garlic, and saute (cook until soft)</li>
<li>Add mince and cook till brown( add any preffered seasonings )</li>
<li>Stir in tomato puree, tomato paste and stock</li>
<li>Leave to simmer for 15 - 25 minutes</li>
</ol>
<div class="gallery-wrapper"><div class="gallery"  data-is-empty="false" data-translation="Add images" data-columns="3">
<figure class="gallery__item"><a href="file:///C:/Users/Leolatahd/Documents/Publii/sites/leos-den/input/media/posts/2/gallery/Mince-2.png_w=800&amp;rev=7219a14f15964a7c8a0acbef22c24f09" data-size="800x450"><img loading="lazy" src="file:///C:/Users/Leolatahd/Documents/Publii/sites/leos-den/input/media/posts/2/gallery/Mince-2.png_w=800&amp;rev=7219a14f15964a7c8a0acbef22c24f09" alt=""></a></figure>
</div></div>
<p>Preheat oven: <strong>180</strong></p>
<p><strong>White Sauce</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Melt butter in a saucepan, add flour and whisk for 1minute</li>
<li>Slowly add warm milk, while whisking, until smooth</li>
<li>Cook until sauce thickens</li>
<li>Add pepper and nutmeg</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Asemble</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>In a baking dish, layer: Lasagne sheets, mince, white sauce ( repeat layers,until;l slightly full )</li>
</ol>
